    "Panel e shows that churn averaged across the 1000 iterations is 2.36 times higher than the null-fixed-reference (t(39958) = 484.613, Cohen's d = 4.849, 95% CI = (15.217, 15.340), n = 19980 (references in step 2 not in step 1 to references in step 1000 not in step 999; 20 runs)) and 2.17 times higher than the null-fixedthreshold models (t(39958) = 272.673, Cohen's d = 2.728, 95% CI = (15.103, 15.322), n = 19980).",
